definitions.definition: On the side that is towards the axis or central line, usually on the upper side.
adjacent to the axis, or in vertebrates the notochord.
examples: In zebrafish, the adaxial cells are precursors to the embryonic slow muscle fibers.

main_definition: ( botany ) On the side that is towards the axis or central line, usually on the upper side.
